Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #414322 -  - EPP Server Down    [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0CmXai:ref ]

TextBody:
Hello Alif,

As my colleagues told me, updating the ssl certificate might cause issues on the nginx config side, because the nginx config file also has to be updated sometimes.
We believe that the change to the certificate broke the nginx config which caused the Nginx service not to start. 
When the server was restarted, the nginx config file was automatically updated. But, because you are using different ports for the UI access and for the Client-Server communication, the nginx config file was not updated correctly and caused the Client-Server communication issue.
After replacing the certificates again and then manually updating the nginx config file the issue was solved.

In order to prevent situations like this, please let us know when you are going to replace the certificate in the future and we will assist you with all the needed changes.

Best regards,
Emil

Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #414322 - - EPP Server Down [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0CmXai:ref ]

Hello Alif,

As my colleagues told me, updating the ssl certificate might cause issues on the nginx config side, because the nginx config file also has to be updated sometimes.
We believe that the change to the certificate broke the nginx config which caused the Nginx service not to start.
When the server was restarted, the nginx config file was automatically updated. But, because you are using different ports for the UI access and for the Client-Server communication, the nginx config file was not updated correctly and caused the Client-Server communication issue.
After replacing the certificates again and then manually updating the nginx config file the issue was solved.

In order to prevent situations like this, please let us know when you are going to replace the certificate in the future and we will assist you with all the needed changes.

Best regards,
Emil

From: Netwrix Support <techsupport@netwrix.com>
Sent: Monday, July 15, 2024 5:59 PM
To: Alif Wahid <Alif.Wahid@gds.ey.com>
Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #414322 - - EPP Server Down [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0CmXai:ref ]



 

Hello Alif,

As my colleagues told me, updating the ssl certificate might cause issues on the nginx config side, because the nginx config file also has to be updated sometimes.
We believe that the change to the certificate broke the nginx config which caused the Nginx service not to start. 
When the server was restarted, the nginx config file was automatically updated. But, because you are using different ports for the UI access and for the Client-Server communication, the nginx config file was not updated correctly and caused the Client-Server communication issue.
After replacing the certificates again and then manually updating the nginx config file the issue was solved.

In order to prevent situations like this, please let us know when you are going to replace the certificate in the future and we will assist you with all the needed changes.

Best regards,
Emil
